commit.message: Capitalized first letter of date thats pushed to the calendar page
back button bug fixed (was linked to addToCalendarAction b/c was copy-pasted)
Added more text color and font attribute correction but fonts are still not correct 100% of the time
Partial fix of weird formatting of changed date/time picker values (by manually reseting color)

Prints out errors if the dates given to the calendar are out of order or there is some other issue. Also, now the date parser (from the output of the poster) now finds dates regardless of whether written in capital or lowercase letters
minor fix with time parsing (forgot to account for pm), and error messages improved in the calendar event page
can't click until information has been processed
Now, titles are found from posters by looking at the largest text! and it seems to be working pretty well!!!!!!
Segue was causing a many errors -- the issue was the the viewController that the segue was going to was copy pasted and had some not-applicable references to 'outlets' and 'actions'
Minor fix on the location finding -- now its working! (off by one error)
get rid of old api button

Rearranged some code to make things execute on their own and more seamlessly (in terms of things that call the APIs, etc) Also, Noah had the idea to start the processing of the image as soon as it it uploaded, before the person even clicks posterpret, allowing more time for the app to load the image info without seeming slow
Added function to get location from natural language processing and a last screen
